The mutually exclusive setting (`children_are_mutually_exclusive`) on the parent tag ensures that when one priority level is assigned to a task, any existing priority level will be automatically removed. So assigning "Low" to a task that has "High" will remove "High" automatically.

Note that we don't need to manually assign the `children_are_mutually_exclusive` parameter to the child tags - this is an inheritance characteristic from the parent tag.

